jhelp.util.io

Interface Binarizable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    UtilIOTest.TestBinarizable

    public interface Binarizable
    Indicates that an object is binarizable.
    A binarizable object is easy to transfer over stream.
    A binarizable object MUST have at least a public empty constructor.
    See ByteArray.readBinarizable(Class), ByteArray.readBinarizableArray(Class), ByteArray.writeBinarizable(Binarizable), ByteArray.writeBinarizableArray(Binarizable...), UtilIO.readBinarizable(Class, java.io.InputStream), UtilIO.readBinarizableNamed(java.io.InputStream), UtilIO.writeBinarizable(Binarizable, java.io.OutputStream) and UtilIO.writeBinarizableNamed(Binarizable, java.io.OutputStream) for transfer binarizables
    Author:
    JHelp
